---
import PatternLayout from '../../../../layouts/PatternLayout.astro';

const featureCardStyles = `layout-card[data-variant="outlined"] \{
  transition: box-shadow var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-default),
              border-color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-default);
\}

layout-card[data-variant="outlined"]:hover \{
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-m);
  border-color: var(--color-border-strong);
\}`;

const featureIconStyles = `.feature-icon \{
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 3rem;
  height: 3rem;
  background: var(--color-interactive-subtle);
  color: var(--color-interactive);
  border-radius: var(--radius-m);
\}`;

const alternatingRowStyles = `.feature-row:nth-child(even) \{
  flex-direction: row-reverse;
\}`;

const checkmarkListStyles = `.checkmark-list \{
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
\}

.checkmark-list li \{
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: var(--size-s);
  padding: var(--size-xs) 0;
\}

.checkmark-list icon-wc \{
  color: var(--color-success);
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 0.125em;
\}`;
---

<PatternLayout
  title="Feature Patterns"
  description="Feature section patterns for marketing sites. Icon grids, alternating layouts, card grids, and feature highlights."
  patternName="Features"
  category="marketing"
  currentPath="/docs/patterns/marketing/features/"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Feature sections highlight product capabilities and benefits. These patterns use <code>data-layout="grid"</code> for responsive multi-column layouts and <code>data-layout="sidebar"</code> for split content, applied directly to semantic HTML elements without wrapper elements.</p>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Icon Grid</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A responsive grid of features with icons. Uses <code>data-layout="grid"</code> with <code>data-layout-min="250px"</code> to create columns that automatically adjust based on available space. The outer <code>&lt;section&gt;</code> combines center and gap via <code>data-layout="center"</code> with <code>data-layout-gap</code>, eliminating a nested stack wrapper.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/features-icon-grid.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/features-icon-grid"
      title="Icon Grid Features"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Feature grid with icons">&lt;section class="features" data-layout="center" data-layout-max="wide" data-layout-gap="2xl"&gt;
  &lt;header class="features-header" data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="s"&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;Everything you need to build faster&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Our platform provides all the tools and features you need to ship products quickly without compromising on quality.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/header&gt;
  &lt;div data-layout="grid" data-layout-min="250px" data-layout-gap="l"&gt;
    &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="s"&gt;
      &lt;span class="feature-icon"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="zap" size="md"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Lightning Fast&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Optimized for speed with minimal overhead. Your pages load instantly, keeping users engaged.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="s"&gt;
      &lt;span class="feature-icon"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="shield" size="md"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;h3&gt;Secure by Default&lt;/h3&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Built-in security best practices protect your data and your users without extra configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;!-- Additional features... --&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Styling</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Icon container styles for the colored icon badges:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="Feature icon container">{featureIconStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Alternating Rows</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Feature rows with image and text that alternate sides. Uses <code>data-layout="sidebar"</code> directly on each <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> with CSS to flip the direction on even rows.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/features-alternating.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/features-alternating"
      title="Alternating Features"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Alternating image/text rows">&lt;section class="features" data-layout="center" data-layout-max="wide" data-layout-gap="3xl"&gt;
  &lt;article class="feature-row" data-layout="sidebar" data-layout-gap="2xl" data-layout-sidebar-width="wide" data-layout-content-min="50"&gt;
    &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="m"&gt;
      &lt;h2&gt;Intuitive drag-and-drop builder&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Create beautiful layouts without writing code. Our visual builder lets you design pages quickly with a library of pre-built components.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;a href="#" class="feature-link"&gt;
        Learn about the builder
        &lt;icon-wc name="arrow-right" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
      &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figure class="feature-image" aria-label="Builder interface"&gt;
      Builder Preview
    &lt;/figure&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
  &lt;article class="feature-row" data-layout="sidebar" data-layout-gap="2xl" data-layout-sidebar-width="wide" data-layout-content-min="50"&gt;
    &lt;!-- Second row automatically flips via CSS --&gt;
    &lt;!-- Same structure, image appears on left --&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Styling</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A single rule flips the sidebar direction on even rows:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="Alternating row styles">{alternatingRowStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Card Grid</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Features displayed in bordered cards with hover effects. Uses <code>data-layout="grid"</code> with <code>&lt;layout-card data-variant="outlined"&gt;</code> for base card styling and a small CSS addition for hover states.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/features-card-grid.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/features-card-grid"
      title="Card Grid Features"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Card-based feature grid">&lt;section class="features" data-layout="center" data-layout-max="wide" data-layout-gap="2xl"&gt;
  &lt;header class="features-header" data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="s"&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;Built for modern workflows&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;p class="lead"&gt;Streamline your development process with features designed to help teams move faster.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/header&gt;
  &lt;div data-layout="grid" data-layout-min="280px" data-layout-gap="l"&gt;
    &lt;layout-card data-variant="outlined" data-padding="l"&gt;
      &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="m"&gt;
        &lt;span class="feature-icon"&gt;
          &lt;icon-wc name="zap" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        &lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Instant Deploys&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;p&gt;Push to git and your site is live in seconds. Zero-config deployments with automatic rollbacks.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/layout-card&gt;
    &lt;!-- Additional cards... --&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Styling</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Hover effects on <code>&lt;layout-card&gt;</code> — the component handles base border, padding, and radius:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="Feature card styles">{featureCardStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Feature Highlight</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <p>A spotlight section for a single key feature. Uses <code>data-layout="sidebar"</code> on an <code>&lt;article&gt;</code> with a large image and detailed description including bullet points with checkmarks.</p>
    </layout-text>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/patterns/demos/features-highlight.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/features-highlight"
      title="Feature Highlight"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" label="Single feature spotlight">&lt;section class="feature-highlight" data-layout="center" data-layout-max="wide"&gt;
  &lt;article data-layout="sidebar" data-layout-gap="2xl" data-layout-sidebar-width="wide" data-layout-content-min="45"&gt;
    &lt;figure class="feature-image" aria-label="AI Assistant interface"&gt;
      Feature Illustration
    &lt;/figure&gt;
    &lt;div data-layout="stack" data-layout-gap="l"&gt;
      &lt;layout-badge data-variant="subtle" data-color="primary" data-size="lg"&gt;
        &lt;icon-wc name="star" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
        New Feature
      &lt;/layout-badge&gt;
      &lt;h2&gt;Meet your AI-powered assistant&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Our intelligent assistant helps you work smarter, not harder. It learns your preferences over time and provides personalized suggestions.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;ul class="checkmark-list"&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;
          &lt;icon-wc name="check" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;Natural language processing understands complex requests&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;li&gt;
          &lt;icon-wc name="check" size="sm"&gt;&lt;/icon-wc&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;Learns from your workflow to provide relevant suggestions&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;!-- Additional bullet points... --&gt;
      &lt;/ul&gt;
      &lt;div data-layout="cluster" data-layout-gap="m"&gt;
        &lt;a href="#" class="button"&gt;Try It Free&lt;/a&gt;
        &lt;a href="#" class="button ghost"&gt;Watch Demo&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/article&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</code-block>

    <h3>Styling</h3>
    <layout-text>
      <p>Checkmark list styles for benefit bullet points:</p>
    </layout-text>

    <code-block language="css" label="Checkmark list styles">{checkmarkListStyles}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Usage Notes</h2>
    <layout-text>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Icon Grid:</strong> Best for listing 4–8 capabilities at a glance. Each item is short — a heading and one sentence.</li>
        <li><strong>Alternating Rows:</strong> Use when each feature needs a supporting image or illustration. Works well for 2–4 features with deeper descriptions.</li>
        <li><strong>Card Grid:</strong> Choose when features are peers and benefit from visual separation. Hover effects signal interactivity — pair with links if cards are clickable.</li>
        <li><strong>Feature Highlight:</strong> Use to spotlight a single flagship feature with a benefit checklist and call-to-action. Place after a grid variant for emphasis.</li>
        <li><strong>Combining variants:</strong> A common pattern is Icon Grid for an overview, followed by Alternating Rows or a Feature Highlight for deeper dives.</li>
        <li><strong>Semantic markup:</strong> Use <code>data-layout</code> attributes on semantic elements like <code>&lt;section&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;article&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;header&gt;</code> instead of nesting layout wrapper elements.</li>
      </ul>
    </layout-text>
  </section>

